Date:  18/11/1933
Source:  Press, The
Author:
Vol / Page:  15
Edition:
Quote:  Rep.- Sometimes shed r. Under the arbitration award it is laid down that `the shearers should elect a representative' who deals with the employer whenever any dispute or question arises.  If the r. is a sensible man of good will, shearing goes through with hardly a hitch. (C.)
